@AdamShellard But cells also migrate in bed of other cells or confined between tissues. Like muscle cells, I wonder if migrating cells can influence those cells biochemically to change stiffness.
@AdamShellard Interesting. I can only think of stuff done in cancer cells in collagen. Nothing really in vivo. Though it is hard to assume that it can be purely mechanical.

@AdamShellard I agree.  So are you thinking in terms of mechanics of cells migrating affecting stiffness of neighboring cells or biochemically migrating cells would influence neighboring cells in the niche.  Like by secreting some signaling molecules.
@AdamShellard Lol okay. Let me know if you find one. Tissue stiffness is hard to measure in vivo. I wonder how many studies are out there about it.
